(Fig. 3). DFT calculations on ordered cation systems show that in (I) occupation of site 19 by $\mathrm{Rb}$ is disfavored by $0.19 \mathrm{kcal}$ $\mathrm{mol}^{-1}$, while in (II) occupation of this site by $\mathrm{K}$ is favored by $0.28 \mathrm{kcal} \mathrm{mol}^{-1}$. These trends are consistent with the refined occupancies, but the energy differences are within the expected errors for such calculations.

For (I), the root-mean-square Cartesian displacement of the non- $\mathrm{H}$ atoms of the citrate anion in the disordered refined structure and the ordered DFT-optimized structures is $0.114$, $0.080$, and $0.079 \AA$ for $\mathrm{Rb}$ at site 19, 20, and 21 (Fig. 4). The average absolute difference in the cation positions is

